{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Unknown origin, though came to be associated with French [[dormire]] ‘sleep’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈdɔːmaʊs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dormice}}

# Any of several species of small, mostly [[European]] [[rodent]]s of the family ''[[Gliridae]]''; also called ''[[Myoxidae]]'' or ''[[Muscardinidae]]'' by some taxonomists.
# (Figurative) A person who sleeps a great deal, or who falls asleep readily (by analogy with the sound hibernation of the dormouse). 

